<TITLE> UK envoy sees fair election results </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 3 (bdnews24.com)  The British high commissioner has said he believes emergency rule should end prior to the election and there should be no plausible reason to reject the outcome if the voting is fair. Stephen Evans made the observation at a dialogue arranged by the Diplomatic Correspondents' Association of Bangladesh at the National Press Club on Wednesday. Speaking about rejection of polls results, Evans said, "There's no reason why one should reject the results when the election process has been transparent and fair all through." "Well, under a democracy, the opposition will criticise the treasury policies and vibrant debates will ensue, of course." To cope globally with the ongoing financial crisis, he said instituting democratic governance in countries such as Bangladesh also appears to be of paramount importance. "Enhancing cooperation between nations has also become a necessity to combat terrorists and root out terrorism" said the UK envoy. The dialogue session was presided over by the DCAB president Masud Karim and conducted by its general secretary Rahid Ejaz. bdnew
